bilingual.source: He gets frustrated when things don't go as planned.
bilingual.target: 当事情不按计划进行时，他会感到沮丧的。

bilingual.source: The team was frustrated by their continuous losses.
bilingual.target: 团队因连续的失败而感到沮丧的。

bilingual.source: He felt frustrated because he couldn't solve the problem.
bilingual.target: 他因为无法解决问题而感到沮丧的。

bilingual.source: She was frustrated with the slow progress of the project.
bilingual.target: 她对项目的进展缓慢感到沮丧的。

bilingual.source: She felt frustrated after failing the exam for the third time.
bilingual.target: 她在第三次考试失败后感到沮丧的。

bilingual.source: So what should a frustrated employee do? Here are some tips
bilingual.target: 那么，沮丧的员工到底应该怎么做？

bilingual.source: It was the daily life of the farm, with its repetitive tasks, that frustrated him.
bilingual.target: 使他感到沮丧的是农场的日常生活和单调重复和劳动。

bilingual.source: If you offer too few moves, like if you take away jumping, players can get very frustrated.
bilingual.target: 如果你提供的招式过少，比如，你把跳跃动作卸掉，玩家会非常沮丧的。

bilingual.source: Thus, Singh and his reformist allies often seem to be sitting, frustrated, on the sidelines.
bilingual.target: 于是，辛格与他的改革盟友们似乎时常束手无策，成为沮丧的旁观者。

bilingual.source: "If there weren't such a thing as football, we'd all be frustrated footballers. " - Mick Lyons.
bilingual.target: 如果这个世上并不存在足球，那么我们都将是沮丧的足球球员。

yingyinNormal.en: I was just frustrated because my career is going nowhere.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当时我因为事业不顺，内心严重受挫。

yingyinNormal.en: You don't know what it's like to feel completely frustrated.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不能理解这种闹心的感觉是何滋味。

yingyinNormal.en: I was stressed, and I was frustrated. And quite frankly, I was, actually, I was embarrassed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 压力感与挫败感油然而生，说实话，当时感觉身陷窘境。

yingyinNormal.en: He's frustrated by all the families who are giving in. The axe falls and they do nothing to fight back.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为那些放弃希望的家族让他很失望，困难来了，他们却无所作为。

yingyinNormal.en: Look, I'm sorry if you're frustrated, but our job is to investigate how a plane ended up in the Hudson River.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我并无意想惹恼你，可我们的工作就是去调查飞机掉进哈德逊河的原因。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, it's okay to feel frustrated when things aren't going your way. I suppose. Maybe it's not that big a deal.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当事情不如意的时候感到不爽也是很正常的。我想是吧。也许这没什么大不了的。

yingyinNormal.en: But the problem is economies can take a long time to reach their equilibrium and may even stall along the way. And in the meantime people can get a little frustrated.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但问题是经济得需要很多时间才能达到出入平衡，而且还有可能什么进展都没有。所以在这时，人们对这样的作法可能会有点失望。

examination_example.sentence: Sometimes parents get exhausted and <highlight>frustrated</highlight> and are unable to maintain a tolerant and composed style with their kids.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有时父母会感到疲惫和沮丧，无法对孩子保持宽容和沉着的态度。
